## Where To Build Your Own vs Use Third‑Party

**High‑leverage to build yourself (aligns with your moats):**

- Tap919 Middleman (FastAPI + metrics + usage events).
- Cloudflare Worker gateway + “Edge storefront” behavior.
- Capability Registry and agentic interfaces (`tm.*`, `sc.*`, `bm.*`).
- AetherDesk as the operator + Runner dashboard (usage, payouts, policy).
- Affiliate Runner system (tracking, commissions, kits) on top of Middleman.
- StreetCode (IDE) and BlackMind (model/CRISPR surface).

**Low‑leverage to build yourself (use third‑party):**

- Card payments, invoices, tax (Stripe).
- Core DB and data infra (managed Postgres, basic storage).
- Deep observability stack (start with hosted or OSS; don’t invent OTEL).
- Full accounting system and legal stack.
- Commodity dev tooling (Git hosting, CI/CD, chat, project tracking).

